        <h1 class="goldtext">Introducing the ACL Call of Duty: Ghosts League</h1>
        <p class="smalltext"><i>August 4 2014 by Beware</i></p>
        <p>We’ve hinted at it before, and now we are happy to announce, ACL’s very first online league for Call of Duty: Ghosts. What a better way to say goodbye to Ghosts and prepare for the upcoming release of Advance Warfare than to pit Australia & New Zealand’s best teams against each other, covering the action live from our new broadcast office in Sydney on mlg.tv.</p>


		<p>Hosting ANZ’s 8 best teams, players will compete twice a week for a period of 7 weeks, ending in a 4 team Playoff bracket. At the end of the Regular Season, the four best teams based on Win/Loss ratio will compete in the Single Elimination Playoff bracket for the title of ANZ Call of Duty: Ghosts Champions and the lion’s share of the Prize Pool. For more information, read below:</p>

